                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107027">Clapcote</placeName>.
                             
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> de la <surname>Sale</surname>
                        </persName> son and heir of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de la <surname>Sale</surname>
                        </persName> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of Clement</surname>, clerk</persName>, for 40/- (1) 2 parts of an acre of arable land in <placeName type="minor">Golasfurlonghetum</placeName> the land of N. f. C. and the land which <persName nymRef="Sale">
                           <forename>Agnes</forename>, mother of T. de la S.</persName> held in dower, reaching south to the prior’s long acre; (2) ½ acre of arable land in the same shot between the said Agnes’ land on each side. Rent: a gillieflower. 
                            Witnesses: <persName>Sir <forename>John</forename> de <surname>St. John</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Mackenaye [Macknay]</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Luchiis</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Sottewelle</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Brihtwaltone</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Andrew</forename> de <surname>Butelor</surname>
                        </persName>’,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Huberd</surname>
                        </persName>. 
                            <origDate notBefore-custom="1270" notAfter="1280" precision="low">
                           <supplied>c. 1270–80.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                        </p>
